{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Renamed files appear in their own category and are not also counted as a deletion plus an addition.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure boundary is real git rename semantics plus CLI categorization. MOCK-MISS: a unit test of counting logic can pass while the git invocation emits add/delete instead of rename due to real diff options/thresholds. REAL-INFRA and MOCK-HIDE: this behavior depends on real subprocess git output from an actual repo rename, so in-process fakes can hide the failure. LLM-DEP/MULTI-STEP: not applicable.","test_description":"Create a temporary real git repo, commit a file, rename it, and run the CLI as a subprocess against that repo. Assert stdout report shows the file only in renamed, and added/deleted counts do not include that rename.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.72,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Diffs that include binary files do not cause the tool to crash; binary files are counted in the output.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA: binary handling failures often occur at subprocess I/O/encoding boundaries with real git output. MOCK-HIDE: mocked text diffs may never reproduce binary markers/bytes that trigger decode or parser crashes. Not LLM-related.","test_description":"In a temp git repo, commit a binary file change (and optionally mixed text+binary changes), run the CLI subprocess, and assert exit code is success and report includes binary file counts.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.85,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Running the tool on a repository that has no commits yet produces an empty report rather than an error.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior text is explicitly about a real repository state ('no commits yet')